# Pair programming

<div style="background-color: #a6e3e8; border-radius: 40px 40px 40px 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 0.5px 20px 1px 20px;">

<p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 20px; font-size: 18px; ">
Pair programming is a technique in which two programmers work together at one computer. One, the driver, writes code while the other, the navigator, directs the driver on the design and setup of the code. The two programmers switch roles often. 
 </p>
 
</div>
<br>

## What is my role as the teacher? 

##### As the teacher, you play a critical role in determining and establishing routines for how your students will use the pair programming strategy. 



<img src="https://images.code.org/d54edebfb0b0c6c55393276180ae19f9-image-1639783726177.jpg" alt="Two students high-five each other while sitting at desktop computers." width="300px" style="border-radius:10px; float:right; margin: 0 0 40px 40px;">

## Pair programming has been shown to:

* ##### Improve computer science enrollment, retention, and students' performance.
* ##### Increase students' confidence.
* ##### Develop students' critical thinking skills.
* ##### Introduce students to the ‚Äúreal world‚Äù working environment. In fact, many university courses and computer science professionals use pair programming to help them problem solve!


<div style="clear:both;">
<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
<summary style="font-size: 1.5em; font-weight: bold;">ü§ùüèΩ How do I begin pair programming with my students?</summary>
<div style="margin-top: 20px; margin-left: 20px; margin-right: 20px;">
    <p>

1. ##### Form pairs.
2. ##### Give each pair one computer.
3. ##### Decide upon initial roles (driver or navigator).
4. ##### Have students start working. 
5. ##### Ensure that students switch roles at regular intervals (every 3 to 5 minutes).
6. ##### Ensure that the navigators remain active participants. 
</p></div></details>

<details style="background-color: #ececec; padding: 10px; margin-bottom: 10px; border: 1px solid transparent; border-radius: 5px;">
